{"questionId":"4150199","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The student collects the following data.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:248px;border-color:#000000;width:443.55px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"o\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Gauge pressure Δ<em>p</em> / kPa</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Maximum force <em>F</em><sub>max</sub> / N</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">108</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">133</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">30</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">158</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">40</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">170</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">50</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">188</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">60</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">192</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">70</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">206</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">80</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">220</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The student initially hypothesizes that <em>F</em><sub>max</sub> is proportional to Δ<em>p</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the absolute uncertainty in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>F</mi><mi>max</mi><mn>3</mn></msubsup></math> for Δ<em>p</em> = 30 kPa. State an appropriate number of significant figures for your answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>15 % seen anywhere ✓</p>\n<p>«Δ(<em>F</em><sup>3</sup>) =» 39.4&nbsp;× 10<sup>5</sup>&nbsp;× 0.15 = 5.9 × 10<sup>5</sup> ✓</p>\n<p>±6 × 10<sup>5</sup> ✓</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>MP1</strong> is for the propagation of 5 %. It can be shown differently, e.g. 3 × 5% Allow students to use 40 × 10<sup>5</sup> (from the graph).</em></p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>MP3</strong> for <strong>any</strong> uncertainty rounded to 1 significant digit</em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Award [3]</strong> for a <strong>BCA</strong>.</em></p>\n<p><em>Allow <strong>ECF</strong> from <strong>MP1</strong> and <strong>MP2</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"4150199","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ2.1di","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Calculate the absolute uncertainty in Fmax3 for Δp = 30 kPa. State an appropriate number of significant figures for your answer.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Tools","Tool 3: Mathematics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
